{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"403fb810-5909-43d5-9b12-ee69da060000","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**MSTest v3 drops support for older TFMs.** Your project targets three frameworks that are all problematic:\n\n| Target | Status in MSTest v3 |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ❌ Dropped — minimum is `net6.0` (for .NET) or removed entirely for legacy .NET Framework |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped — EOL, not supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped — EOL, not supported |\n\n**MSTest v3 requires at minimum `net6.0`** (and ideally `net8.0`+). It also consolidates the two packages (`MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter`) into a single **`MSTest`** meta-package.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. **Update your target frameworks** — replace all three with supported ones (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. **Replace the package references** — swap `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` for the single `MSTest` package (v3.x).\n3. **Review breaking API changes** — some attributes and assertions changed behavior in v3.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file to MSTest v3 with compatible target frameworks?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"25d02b6e-a80d-4d70-814c-41b3d358e3f1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me provide details about compatibility issues.","outputTokens":391,"requestId":"BD15:E210B:2316A53:27813F5:6A07DB48"},"id":"8b6aff30-ff21-4d11-8b9a-1d8e5cf480a6","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:49:54.371Z","parentId":"d6b4923d-74d2-46c2-83e5-4259a54c49af"}
